    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>POWER DISTRIBUTION</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Battery Power (Key On or OFF)</title>
            <para>Battery power (key on or off) from B2 feed stud (cab power distribution center) is supplied to sleeper
                fuse panels (582) and (583), and directly powers the sleeper lighting system.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Fuse Panel (582)</emph>
            </para>
            <para>This panel is located in the left sleeper luggage compartment and has four fuse cavities.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>15A fuse 582-A powers TV and VCR</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>10A fuse 582-B powers the auxiliary circulation fan and Salem power vent.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>5A fuse 582-C powers the refrigerator.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Cavity D is not used.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Fuse Panel (583)</emph>
            </para>
            <para>This panel is located in the left sleeper luggage compartment and has four fuse cavities.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>15A fuse 583-A feeds the left auxiliary power source.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>15A fuse 583-B feeds the right auxiliary power source.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Cavities C and D are unused.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Ground System</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08007_25.xml" xrefid="f0800727"></hotlnk>
                for a diagram of the sleeper ground system.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
